> This veggie moussaka is Mimi's absolute favourite! It's packed with awesome aubergines and lovely lentils. It's perhaps not on the same scale as the Parthenon but it's a lot tastier. Enjoy!

Trim the @aubergine{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} with a #garlic press{} (or use a garlic press).

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until soft and golden, ~{6-7%minutes}. Add the @dried oregano{1}, @tomato purée{15%g}, @ground cinnamon{1} and half the garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Next, stir in the @red split lentils{50%g}, @Worcester sauce{7.5%ml}, @vegetable stock powder{1} and @finely chopped tomatoes{1}. Add the @water{750%ml} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Stir, bring to the boil, lower the heat to medium-low and simmer until the lentils are soft (but still have a slight bite to them), ~{20-25%minutes}. If the sauce gets too dry, just add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, lay the aubergine slices on a #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle over a good glug of oil. Season with salt and pepper. Grill until browned and soft, about ~{8-9%minutes} on each side.

> Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn. If they aren't soft after this time, just leave them under your grill for another 2-3 mins.

Remove and set aside.

In a #small bowl{}, mix the remaining garlic with the olive oil. Cut the @ciabatta{1} in half (as though making a sandwich) and smear the garlic oil over the cut side.

When the tomato sauce is ready, transfer the sauce to an #ovenproof dish{}. Layer over the aubergine slices. Dollop over the @creme fraiche{75%g} and then spread it out evenly across the top.

Sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} over the moussaka and season with pepper. Grill until the cheese is golden and bubbling, about ~{5-6%minutes}.

Remove from the grill, pop the garlic bread under the grill and toast until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Serve the moussaka in bowls with the cheat's garlic bread on the side. Enjoy!